{"id": "block-context-blob", "phase": "data", "level": "high", "pillar": true, "load_bearing": true, "decision": "How does each block get the grounding context the chatbot answers FROM?", "plain": "Each block's chatbot grounds in BOTH its own content (local {title,text}) AND the whole plan (global goal + all decisions/blocks + glossary).", "choice": "LOCAL + GLOBAL grounding (operator-confirmed). LOCAL: DATA.blocks[block_id]={title, the block's rendered text (tags stripped)}. GLOBAL: a shared DATA.context = goal + glossary + a one-line index of every decision AND every block. The widget's system prompt injects the block's local {title,text} FIRST (answer THIS section) then the global context (so it can cross-reference the rest of the plan). Extends today's grounding (viz.py:514 already has goal+glossary) with per-block local text + an all-decisions/blocks index.", "principle": "ground-in-the-block-content", "status": "verified", "why": "the whole feature rests on this: if a block has no extractable text (pure visual), the chatbot has nothing to ground on and hallucinates. Cheapest kill test: pull one block's text and check it's enough to answer a real question. VERIFIED 2026-07-02 (block_context_probe.py on real asr_rewrite): assembled 4 block context blobs from the same sources viz renders from (DATA 2140 chars, FOCUS 1582, pipeline 191, WANT 291) -- every block yields extractable grounding text, 'pure-visual' concern unfounded. Grounding kill-test 2/2: asked block-specific questions, the LOCAL+GLOBAL system prompt produced grounded answers (data-section -> real JSONL input/target format w/ example; current-focus -> the bootstrap/distill arms). Local+global grounding works.", "examples": [{"cap": "LOCAL: each block's own content in the tl-data blob", "code": "DATA.blocks[\"data-section\"] = {\"title\": \"DATA — what the rewriter reads & writes\", \"text\": \"Web text {\\\"text\\\":...} JSONL -> LoRA rewriter -> <|speaker:N|> [tag] -> s2 text source (137 pairs)\"}"}, {"cap": "GLOBAL: a shared index so any block's chatbot can cross-reference", "code": "DATA.context = {\"goal\": \"...\", \"decisions\": [\"faithfulness: allow dramatize, factual gate\", \"teacher-and-quality-filter: Claude+fact-precision gate\", ...], \"blocks\": [\"DATA\", \"CURRENT FOCUS\", \"pipeline\", ...]}"}, {"cap": "The block system prompt = LOCAL first, then GLOBAL", "code": "sysPromptBlock(b) = 'You answer about ONE section: '+b.title+'\\nContent: '+b.text+'\\n\\nFULL PLAN (for cross-reference): goal='+DATA.context.goal+'; decisions='+DATA.context.decisions.join('; ')"}], "match": "(block.?context|tl-data|DATA\\.blocks|grounding|title.?text)", "artifact": "/home/shiyil/asr/report-block-chatbot/block_context_probe.py"}
{"id": "generic-widget", "phase": "impl", "level": "high", "pillar": true, "decision": "Reuse the existing per-decision widget, or write a new one?", "plain": "Generalize the one existing chatbot widget from decision-keyed to block-keyed; don't fork a second copy.", "choice": "GENERALIZE the existing tl-chat JS (viz.py:475-600): make it read data-block/DATA.blocks with a block system prompt, reusing the SAME fetch/key/localStorage machinery. Decisions become one KIND of block. NOT a second parallel widget.", "principle": "one-widget-many-blocks", "status": "verified", "why": "a forked second widget duplicates the API/key/memory code and drifts; generalizing keeps one code path. The decision-specific sysPrompt becomes a special case of the block sysPrompt. VERIFIED 2026-07-02: Generalized the ONE tl-chat widget to read data-dec OR data-block (viz.py): decisions are one KIND of block, reusing the same fetch/key/localStorage/memory machinery -- no forked second widget. Added sysPromptBlock (local title+text) + globalCtx (all-decisions index) so grounding is LOCAL+GLOBAL. Rendered asr_rewrite: 9 decision chatbots preserved + 4 block chatbots (DATA/FOCUS/pipeline/WHAT WE WANT); browser-equivalent smoke test: the pipeline block answers grounded ('Web text -> LoRA rewriter -> ...').", "not_this": "fork a second parallel chatbot widget just for the new blocks, duplicating the API/key/memory JS", "not_re": "(second|new|separate|parallel|another) (widget|chatbot|tl-chat)", "match": "(generic.?widget|generaliz|reuse.?widget|data-block|one.?widget)", "artifact": "/home/shiyil/.claude/plugins/cache/trainlint/trainlint/0.3.36/research/viz.py"}
