{"id": "view-via-local-server", "phase": "deliver", "level": "high", "pillar": false, "decision": "How do you actually SEE the JS chatbots — the Claude app inline-render strips JS?", "plain": "trainlint silently auto-starts a loopback web server on render, so the JS-heavy report (chatbots) is viewable in a real browser.", "choice": "On every render, viz.py silently ensures a loopback http server (serve.py, 127.0.0.1 ONLY -- fixes http.server's 0.0.0.0 default) is up for the viz output dir, and prints a SERVE: URL. The chatbots need JS (browser API calls), so an inline JS-stripped preview shows none; a real browser over the server (SSH -L) runs them. Opt-out via TRAINLINT_SERVE=0.", "principle": "serve-the-js-report-silently", "status": "verified", "artifact": "/home/shiyil/.claude/plugins/cache/trainlint/trainlint/0.3.36/research/serve.py", "why": "the per-block chatbot is JS-injected (createElement) + calls the Anthropic API from the browser -- a JS-stripped inline render shows NO button at all (the operator saw exactly this: '没看到chatbot'). A local server is the only way to run the JS. VERIFIED 2026-07-02: render auto-starts exactly one loopback server (ss shows 1 LISTEN on 127.0.0.1:8420), HTTP 200, idempotent across renders, TRAINLINT_SERVE=0 opts out, binds 127.0.0.1 only.", "match": "(serve|local server|http.server|loopback|127\\.0\\.0\\.1|browse.*report|view.*chatbot)"}
